To use antlr4 library in an external project do the following:

Set the cmake variables from the external project
        set(ANTLR4_GRAMMAR_FILE "${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/grammar/egc.g4")
        set(ANTLR4_GRAMMAR_NAME "egc")
        set(ANTLR4_BASE_RULE_NAME "formula")


Set the following include paths to be able to access antlr4 data structures:

include_directories(${CMAKE_BINARY_DIR}/include)
# due to cpp runtime bug this include must also be set
include_directories(${CMAKE_BINARY_DIR}/include/antlr4-runtime)
include_directories(${CMAKE_BINARY_DIR}/parser_gen)


Reimplement the functions defined in the generated <GRAMMAR>BaseVisitor.h file.


Set the C++11 compiler flags for the antlr files
        set_property(TARGET egc_gramar_test PROPERTY CXX_STANDARD 11)
        set_property(TARGET egc_gramar_test PROPERTY CXX_STANDARD_REQUIRED ON)

        
Link to the antlr4 runtime library and the library parser generated library:        
        target_link_libraries(egc_gramar_test antlr4_parser_generated_static antlr4_static)

        
For further information have a look at the example code (example directory of this project)        
